 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Themiscryian War Queen</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#993300>(5/5/03 8:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=212>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Attack is over</span><hr size=1> Solari kept an eye on the unconscious leader as he laid in the mud, tied up. If he were to awake and try to get free, her horse would begin to drag him thru the mud. She fought off another Roman, who was either scared or stupid as he yelled and ran towards her. Solari threw the roman sword at him, seeing it land its mark as it went thru his chest and reeling him backwards into the mud.<br>
She looked around her once more to see how many Romans were left fighting. upon seeing that their numbers were reduced to just a few, she gave the call, signaling that their attack was over with and for those few remaining Romans either be killed or taken as prisonares to be dealt with later. <br>
She walked back over to the Roman leader and made sure that the ropes were still tied tight around him. She walked over and picked up her war mask from the mud, shook it off, then placed it back on, feeling blood and mud mix on her face. <br>
Solari mounted up on her horse, looked around the village and noticed that there were shadowed faces staring at her from within the safety of huts. A few moments later, a woman and her children, a boy and girl, came out to stand before Solari's warhorse. <br>
<br>
&quot;Please, do not kill my son.&quot; She pleaded in her roman accent. <br>
<br>
Solari looked down at them, lifted up her mask and smiled softly. <br>
&quot;I have no desire to kill your son.&quot; She said softly. &quot;Your family will be safe now, if you so desire it.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 359<br> <font color=#993300>(5/5/03 11:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=213>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack is over</span><hr size=1> The woman again turned back to the other young girls. She was not such a woman though. Her husband was one of the elder generals who bought her off of her Father when she was fourteen, and that was only three years ago.<br>
&quot;Don't you fools get it? We're free!&quot; She yelled.<br>
<br>
However, her general husband came up behind her grabbing her around the neck. &quot;I wouldn't get so ahead of yourself Tahira!&quot; He growled.<br>
<br>
Alysia turned her wolf eyes back towards the scene and narrowed her eyes. She shouted out and tossed the young girl a dagger.<br>
<br>
The other women screached and ducked, but as soon as the blade was in sight, Tahira caught it and jammed it into the chest of her Roman husband. Soon, the General dropped to the floor and Tahira stood over the body narrowing her eyes down at it. With a swift kick, she hit him in the ribs and turned her eyes to the dagger that had a white wolf imprinted on the hilt. <br>
Her eyes turned upwards to where Alysia was looking at her.<br>
<br>
Alysia grinned a bit and looked back to Odessa.<br>
&quot;This one's comming to Scynthia.&quot; She smirked a bit and then looked back to her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come on girl. Come enjoy freedom.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a grin, the girl smiled and left the hut following Alysia into the woods.<br>
The Scynthian Queen turned back and shouted to her wolves.<br>
<br>
&quot;Anything that's wounded, kill it. Any Roman that's alive, bring them to deal with later.&quot;<br>
<br>
Needless to say, the Scynthian wolves ended up taking only three Romans back to the lands. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
